{"person":{"id":"H00890","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":6,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"X00479","mother_id":"H00370"},"tags":["illinois_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","entry":"890"},{"short":"Brockett genealogy (Descendants of John Brockett)"}],"birth":{"year":1780},"death":{"year":1857},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"X00485","children_ids":["HD1511","HD1512","HD1513","HD1514","HD1515","HD1517","HD1516","HD1518","HD1519"],"marriage_number":1}],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Lyman Brockett","first_name":"Lyman","last_name":"Brockett","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Three sons died violent maritime deaths","body":"Three of Lyman Brockett's sons died violent maritime deaths within the same generation: Miles (born 1805) was killed by a shark while in the West Indies around 1826 at age twenty-one; Loyal (born 1811) died at sea in 1829 of yellow fever as a ship officer at age eighteen; and Lyman Goodsell (born 1823) was a ship officer who died in the East Indies. The compressed family loss across three sons in the merchant and whaling trades captured the maritime risk of mid-nineteenth-century American shipping."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Four or five sons in shipping and whaling","body":"Beyond the three sons who died at sea, Lyman's son Lewis (born 1808) died in New Haven after returning from a three-year whaling voyage, unmarried — suggesting illness contracted on the voyage. The family was a maritime-trade family in concentration: five of nine children had ocean-going careers. The eldest son Merrick later moved inland to Peoria Illinois, where his father Lyman eventually joined him."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Connecticut to Illinois migration in old age","body":"After his New Haven-area maritime family had been scattered or lost to the sea, Lyman Brockett moved to Rosefield Illinois in his old age and died there around 1857. He is buried at Peoria Illinois — joining his eldest son Merrick who had migrated west earlier. His wife Hannah Goodsell of Watertown Connecticut had predeceased him by about two years in 1855."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Born North Haven 1780, nine children with Hannah","body":"Lyman Brockett was born July 25, 1780 in North Haven Connecticut (baptized September 7, 1780) and married Hannah Goodsell of Watertown Connecticut. Nine children: Merrick, Miles, Lewis, Loyal, Lucy Charlotte (married Isaac Jones and removed to Oregon; remarried William Jones), Russell (died in infancy), Harvey Russell (named for grandmother Hannah Russell Pierpont's family), Mary Ann, and Lyman Goodsell."}],"slug":"lyman-brockett-1780"},"neighborhood":{"focus":{"id":"H00890","slug":"lyman-brockett-1780","n":"Lyman Brockett","by":1780,"dy":1857,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":6},"spouses":[{"order":1,"spouse":{"id":"X00485","slug":"hannah-goodsell-1779","n":"Hannah Goodsell","by":1779,"dy":1855,"sx":"f","hd":false,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":null},"year":null,"children":[{"id":"HD1511","slug":"merrick-brockett-1803","n":"Merrick Brockett","by":1803,"dy":1860,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":7},{"id":"HD1512","slug":"miles-brockett-1805","n":"Miles Brockett","by":1805,"dy":1826,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":7},{"id":"HD1513","slug":"lewis-brockett-1808","n":"Lewis Brockett","by":1808,"dy":null,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":7},{"id":"HD1514","slug":"loyal-bro